						               													<description>Object of the game: &amp;#10;To dislodge opponents clip on heart with a pliable plastic sword.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Before Starting Play:&amp;#10;Each player takes one sword and one Heart that he clips on his person, below his shoulders or above his knees.&amp;#10;The Heart may not be placed on the arms. Any player then takes the arrows and throws them in the air or places them in a circle radius of about six feet , disregarding where the colors may fall. The spinner is then placed in the center of the circle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to play:&amp;#10;Each player stands on the outside pattern of the arrows . The first player then spins the dial . The dial stops on a blue arrow , the players quickly place any foot on any convenient blue arrow , with toes pointing in the direction of the arrow. When the spinner shows geeen players place the other foot on any green arrow . As the game continues , players may place either foot on the arrow that is most convenient to them . When the spinner stops on a Heart, the player calls out &amp;ldquo;HAVE A HEART&amp;rdquo; and each player tries to get each other&amp;rsquo;s heart with his sword. The hearts may be removed by either knocking them off or by placing the curved part of the sword thru the hole in the heart and pulling it off. If a player loses balance and falls or his heart is removed , he is eliminated from the game. The last player remaining is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
